1
00:00:17,727 --> 00:00:20,479
(WATER FLOWING)

2
00:00:26,986 --> 00:00:28,905
(DEVICE CRACKLING)

3
00:00:30,364 --> 00:00:33,034
(PANTING)

4
00:00:35,995 --> 00:00:37,955
(CRANK FLASHLIGHT WHIRRING)

5
00:00:43,336 --> 00:00:44,962
(CRANK FLASHLIGHT WHIRRING)

6
00:00:56,599 --> 00:00:58,351
(MAN GASPS)

7
00:01:03,356 --> 00:01:04,732
(CRACKLING CONTINUES)

8
00:01:28,464 --> 00:01:30,716
(DEVICE CONTINUES CRACKLING)

9
00:02:14,051 --> 00:02:15,678
-(HELICOPTER BLADES WHIRRING)
-(SIGHS)

10
00:02:16,887 --> 00:02:19,765
Is it possible that the water
has already killed them?

11
00:02:20,182 --> 00:02:22,143
Yes.

12
00:02:22,226 --> 00:02:23,769
Then what?

13
00:02:24,979 --> 00:02:26,772
If it doesn't work?

14
00:02:32,695 --> 00:02:34,989
(HELICOPTER APPROACHING)

15
00:02:44,457 --> 00:02:46,876
(DEVICE CRACKLING)

16
00:02:58,512 --> 00:03:00,765
(MUFFLED CONVERSATION)

17
00:03:32,755 --> 00:03:34,673
(BANGING ON DOOR)

18
00:03:39,637 --> 00:03:40,888
(PANTING)

19
00:03:43,182 --> 00:03:45,518
(APPLAUSE)

20
00:03:59,657 --> 00:04:01,158
Get them in the truck.

21
00:04:02,118 --> 00:04:04,245
Get the hoses in! Start pumping!

22
00:04:20,719 --> 00:04:23,639
Uh, I'm here to see
my husband, VASILY Ignatenko.

23
00:04:23,722 --> 00:04:26,183
He's a firefighter from Chernobyl.
I have permission.

24
00:04:26,392 --> 00:04:28,769
Chernobyl? I'm sorry, no visitors.

25
00:04:31,063 --> 00:04:33,482
Well, but Major...
Major Burov told me,

26
00:04:33,566 --> 00:04:34,900
-he said...
-No exceptions.

27
00:04:34,984 --> 00:04:37,778
Please. I've come all the way
from Kievskaya Oblast.

28
00:04:58,174 --> 00:04:59,300
(STAMPS FORM)

29
00:05:03,888 --> 00:05:05,598
Excuse me.

30
00:05:06,932 --> 00:05:08,392
Excuse me, excuse me.

31
00:05:08,476 --> 00:05:09,768
Who are you? What are you doing here?

32
00:05:09,852 --> 00:05:12,646
-I have a pass.
-You can't be here. It's not safe.

33
00:05:12,730 --> 00:05:14,607
I am here to see my husband.

34
00:05:14,690 --> 00:05:15,691
VASILY Ignatenko.

35
00:05:15,774 --> 00:05:17,276
He's a firefighter from Chernobyl.

36
00:05:17,359 --> 00:05:19,820
I know who Ignatenko is,
but you can't.

37
00:05:19,904 --> 00:05:21,906
I have permission. I've...

38
00:05:28,204 --> 00:05:31,582
You can see him for 30 minutes,
not a minute more.

39
00:05:31,665 --> 00:05:34,460
And you cannot touch him in any way.
Do you understand?

40
00:05:34,543 --> 00:05:36,795
-Yeah.
-Room 15.

41
00:05:38,547 --> 00:05:39,548
Thank you.

42
00:05:40,174 --> 00:05:42,051
-You're not pregnant, are you?
-No.

43
00:05:49,975 --> 00:05:51,644
VASILY: I won't have
to give that to you.

44
00:05:51,727 --> 00:05:52,770
MAN: There they are.

45
00:05:53,187 --> 00:05:54,772
No, wait, wait, wait.
I haven't finished yet.

46
00:05:54,855 --> 00:05:55,981
PRAVIK: No, no, he hasn't.

47
00:05:56,774 --> 00:05:58,108
Yeah, that's good.

48
00:06:00,986 --> 00:06:02,238
Yeah, better.

49
00:06:05,157 --> 00:06:06,867
Look who the cat dragged in.

50
00:06:09,495 --> 00:06:11,163
VASILY: What did I tell you?

51
00:06:11,997 --> 00:06:14,333
There's no hiding from you,
is there? Eh?

52
00:06:15,918 --> 00:06:16,919
(GROANS)

53
00:06:17,670 --> 00:06:19,672
Easy, easy. It's okay.

54
00:06:19,755 --> 00:06:23,050
We're all okay. Yeah, we're okay.

55
00:06:33,811 --> 00:06:35,062
(INAUDIBLE)

56
00:06:45,698 --> 00:06:47,783
(HELICOPTER BLADES WHIRRING)

57
00:06:53,372 --> 00:06:55,040
(DEVICE CRACKLING)

58
00:07:33,037 --> 00:07:36,540
How, how, how did this happen?
Who gave them the idea?

59
00:07:36,624 --> 00:07:38,500
-Are you suggesting I did?
-Someone did.

60
00:07:38,584 --> 00:07:42,087
Someone decided
that the evacuation zone

61
00:07:42,171 --> 00:07:45,341
should be 30 kilometers,
when we know, here,

62
00:07:45,424 --> 00:07:48,177
cesium-137 in the Gomel district.

63
00:07:48,260 --> 00:07:50,888
-That's 200 kilometers away!
-It was decided.

64
00:07:50,971 --> 00:07:52,890
-Based on what?
-I don't know!

65
00:07:54,350 --> 00:07:58,270
Forgive me. Maybe I... I've just
spent too much time in my lab.

66
00:07:58,354 --> 00:08:00,022
Or maybe I'm just stupid.

67
00:08:00,814 --> 00:08:02,566
Is this really the way it all works?

68
00:08:03,692 --> 00:08:05,569
An uninformed, arbitrary decision

69
00:08:05,653 --> 00:08:07,905
that will cost who knows
how many lives

70
00:08:07,988 --> 00:08:11,867
made by some apparatchik?
Some career party man?

71
00:08:13,952 --> 00:08:16,038
I'm a career party man.

72
00:08:16,997 --> 00:08:19,792
You should watch your tone,
Comrade Legasov.

73
00:08:20,918 --> 00:08:22,086
PIKALOV: Comrades...

74
00:08:23,128 --> 00:08:25,798
We have visual confirmation
that the fire is nearly extinguished.

75
00:08:25,881 --> 00:08:27,883
There has also been
a reduction in iodine-131

76
00:08:27,966 --> 00:08:29,802
and cesium-137 emissions.

77
00:08:29,885 --> 00:08:31,512
Good. Yes?

78
00:08:32,304 --> 00:08:35,140
But the temperature is rising.

79
00:08:35,224 --> 00:08:36,600
And, uh...

80
00:08:43,774 --> 00:08:46,652
LEGASOV: There's a spike
in zirconium-95.

81
00:08:47,986 --> 00:08:51,198
It's from the cladding
on the fuel rods.

82
00:08:51,281 --> 00:08:53,617
SHCHERBINA: Meaning what?

83
00:08:53,701 --> 00:08:56,078
The meltdown has begun.

84
00:09:25,941 --> 00:09:28,152
(INDISTINCT MOANING IN DISTANCE)

85
00:09:34,700 --> 00:09:36,243
VASILY: Get it off me!

86
00:09:38,871 --> 00:09:41,248
Get it off me!

87
00:09:43,375 --> 00:09:45,210
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

88
00:09:48,756 --> 00:09:50,257
DR. VETROVA: Stop moving!

89
00:09:50,340 --> 00:09:53,093
-Get off him! You're hurting him!
-(SOBBING)

90
00:09:53,927 --> 00:09:56,054
-DOCTOR: You can't be in here.
-What's happening to him?

91
00:09:56,138 --> 00:09:57,598
Get out!

92
00:09:57,681 --> 00:09:59,433
You can't be in here!

93
00:09:59,516 --> 00:10:02,227
(VASILY WAILING)

94
00:10:06,356 --> 00:10:08,734
(SHOUTING CONTINUES)

95
00:10:39,932 --> 00:10:41,016
(PHONE RINGS)

96
00:10:42,392 --> 00:10:43,393
Yes?

97
00:10:43,477 --> 00:10:44,978
MAN ON PHONE: Comrade Shcherbina
is on the phone.

98
00:10:45,062 --> 00:10:46,438
Put him through.

99
00:10:47,898 --> 00:10:49,191
Well?

100
00:10:49,274 --> 00:10:50,943
SHCHERBINA: The fire's nearly out.

101
00:10:51,026 --> 00:10:52,778
The bubbler tanks are being drained.

102
00:10:52,861 --> 00:10:55,823
We have successfully eliminated
the risk of a thermal explosion.

103
00:10:56,782 --> 00:10:58,951
(INHALES DEEPLY)

104
00:10:59,034 --> 00:11:00,035
And?

105
00:11:01,537 --> 00:11:03,163
The situation inside the core

106
00:11:03,247 --> 00:11:06,124
is deteriorating
faster than anticipated.

107
00:11:06,208 --> 00:11:09,086
The concrete pad will last
for six to eight weeks,

108
00:11:09,169 --> 00:11:12,214
but after that, Legasov estimates
a 50% chance

109
00:11:12,297 --> 00:11:14,007
that the fuel will breach the pad

110
00:11:14,091 --> 00:11:16,802
and melt down
into the groundwater itself.

111
00:11:17,761 --> 00:11:20,305
(STAMMERS) And where
does this groundwater go?

112
00:11:20,389 --> 00:11:22,432
The Pripyat River,

113
00:11:22,516 --> 00:11:25,435
which feeds into the Dnieper.

114
00:11:25,519 --> 00:11:28,897
The primary water supply for
approximately 50 million people,

115
00:11:28,981 --> 00:11:33,110
not to mention crops and livestock,
would be unusable.

116
00:11:33,193 --> 00:11:35,904
We're recommending we install
a heat exchanger under the pad

117
00:11:35,988 --> 00:11:39,074
to lower the core temperature
and halt the meltdown.

118
00:11:39,157 --> 00:11:42,202
And in order to do that,
I'm told that we will need

119
00:11:44,538 --> 00:11:48,375
all of the liquid nitrogen
in the Soviet Union.

120
00:11:50,836 --> 00:11:51,837
Oh.

121
00:11:53,005 --> 00:11:54,089
All right.

122
00:11:54,172 --> 00:11:55,757
SHCHERBINA: Yeah, and of course,
we'll also need...

123
00:11:55,841 --> 00:11:57,134
Whatever you need, you have it.

124
00:11:57,217 --> 00:11:58,635
-That should be clear by now.
-Yes.

125
00:11:58,719 --> 00:12:00,304
-Anything else?
-Uh, no, no, no. Thank you.

126
00:12:00,387 --> 00:12:03,432
Yes. I'd like to address
the 30-kilometer exclusion zone.

127
00:12:03,515 --> 00:12:06,268
Wait, what?
Professor Legasov, is that you?

128
00:12:06,351 --> 00:12:07,603
What exclusion zone?

129
00:12:07,686 --> 00:12:09,730
Minor details, General Secretary.

130
00:12:09,813 --> 00:12:12,357
Um, Premier Ryzhkov
has determined that...

131
00:12:12,441 --> 00:12:14,818
If he determined, then he determined.

132
00:12:14,902 --> 00:12:16,320
Look, Professor Legasov,

133
00:12:16,403 --> 00:12:18,322
you are there for one reason only.

134
00:12:18,405 --> 00:12:20,449
Do you understand? To make this stop.

135
00:12:20,532 --> 00:12:21,742
I don't want questions.

136
00:12:21,825 --> 00:12:23,452
I want to know when this will be over.

137
00:12:23,827 --> 00:12:25,871
If you mean when will
Chernobyl be completely safe,

138
00:12:25,954 --> 00:12:29,124
the half-life of plutonium-239
is 24,000 years.

139
00:12:29,207 --> 00:12:32,377
So perhaps we should just say,
"Not within our lifetimes."

140
00:12:34,087 --> 00:12:35,547
(LINE DISCONNECTS)

141
00:12:44,640 --> 00:12:46,516
I think you and I should take a walk.

142
00:12:47,059 --> 00:12:48,727
It's late. I'm tired.

143
00:12:49,811 --> 00:12:52,147
We're taking a walk.

144
00:12:58,612 --> 00:13:01,031
What is it you want? An apology?

145
00:13:02,824 --> 00:13:04,534
Not gonna sit back and...

146
00:13:05,327 --> 00:13:06,370
(LEGASOV SIGHS)

147
00:13:06,453 --> 00:13:08,538
What will happen to our boys?

148
00:13:09,456 --> 00:13:11,875
Which boys? The divers?

149
00:13:11,959 --> 00:13:14,878
The divers, the firefighters,
the men in the control room.

150
00:13:15,587 --> 00:13:18,966
What does the radiation
do to them, precisely?

151
00:13:20,676 --> 00:13:23,303
At the levels
some of them were exposed?

152
00:13:23,387 --> 00:13:26,515
Ionizing radiation tears
the cellular structure apart.

153
00:13:27,474 --> 00:13:30,310
The skin blisters,
turns red, then black.

154
00:13:31,979 --> 00:13:34,481
This is followed by a latency period.

155
00:13:35,691 --> 00:13:37,567
The immediate effects subside.

156
00:13:37,651 --> 00:13:39,403
The patient appears to be recovering.

157
00:13:40,612 --> 00:13:42,990
Healthy, even. But they aren't.

158
00:13:44,616 --> 00:13:47,953
This usually only lasts
for a day or two.

159
00:13:50,455 --> 00:13:51,665
Continue.

160
00:13:53,208 --> 00:13:56,920
Then the cellular damage
begins to manifest.

161
00:13:57,004 --> 00:14:02,384
The bone marrow dies,
the immune system fails,

162
00:14:02,467 --> 00:14:06,179
the organs and soft tissue
begin to decompose.

163
00:14:06,263 --> 00:14:10,308
The arteries and veins
spill open like sieves,

164
00:14:10,392 --> 00:14:12,811
to the point where you can't
even administer morphine

165
00:14:12,894 --> 00:14:16,481
for the pain, which is unimaginable.

166
00:14:17,274 --> 00:14:20,527
And then three days
to three weeks, you're dead.

167
00:14:22,779 --> 00:14:25,032
That is what will happen
to those boys.

168
00:14:27,367 --> 00:14:28,744
And what about us?

169
00:14:32,164 --> 00:14:33,957
Well, we've...

170
00:14:34,041 --> 00:14:37,002
We've gotten a steady dose,
but not as much of it.

171
00:14:38,336 --> 00:14:40,172
Not strong enough to kill the cells,

172
00:14:40,255 --> 00:14:43,300
but consistent enough
to damage our DNA.

173
00:14:44,760 --> 00:14:47,512
So, in time, cancer.

174
00:14:48,055 --> 00:14:51,308
Or a plastic anemia. Either way, fatal.

175
00:14:54,061 --> 00:14:55,353
Well...

176
00:14:57,397 --> 00:15:03,028
In a sense, it would seem we've
gotten off easy then, Valery.

177
00:15:15,707 --> 00:15:17,501
I've seen them before.

178
00:15:23,548 --> 00:15:26,843
SHCHERBINA: Now you know
why I wanted to take a walk.

179
00:15:26,927 --> 00:15:29,179
We can presume
the work site is bugged.

180
00:15:30,180 --> 00:15:34,226
And our rooms, even our bathrooms.

181
00:15:34,309 --> 00:15:36,478
They've been here the whole time.

182
00:15:36,561 --> 00:15:38,563
Of course, they've been here
the whole time.

183
00:15:39,815 --> 00:15:43,693
But if we're seeing them
out in the open now,

184
00:15:43,777 --> 00:15:46,446
it's because they want us to know.

185
00:16:03,213 --> 00:16:04,214
(DOOR OPENS)

186
00:16:05,841 --> 00:16:06,842
(DOOR CLOSES)

187
00:16:28,321 --> 00:16:29,489
KHOMYUK: You've seen that?

188
00:16:31,950 --> 00:16:33,994
The fuel is melting
faster than we expected.

189
00:16:34,077 --> 00:16:36,371
I know. I have a plan.

190
00:16:37,122 --> 00:16:39,708
Heat exchanger, I hope.

191
00:16:39,791 --> 00:16:41,251
Yes.

192
00:16:44,462 --> 00:16:46,381
There's something I've wanted
to ask you, comrade,

193
00:16:46,464 --> 00:16:49,843
but I see you're already asking
yourself the same question.

194
00:16:53,597 --> 00:16:55,849
Why did it explode?

195
00:16:57,559 --> 00:16:59,853
I've worked the numbers over and over,

196
00:16:59,936 --> 00:17:03,523
presuming the worst possible
conditions in an RBMK reactor.

197
00:17:05,525 --> 00:17:08,153
And I always get the same answer.

198
00:17:08,236 --> 00:17:09,654
Which is?

199
00:17:11,072 --> 00:17:12,240
It's not possible.

200
00:17:13,450 --> 00:17:14,868
And yet...

201
00:17:17,954 --> 00:17:20,040
You're not going to solve this here.

202
00:17:21,708 --> 00:17:23,210
Not on paper.

203
00:17:24,920 --> 00:17:26,713
Everyone who was in the control room,

204
00:17:26,796 --> 00:17:29,174
Dyatlov, Akimov, Toptunov,

205
00:17:29,257 --> 00:17:32,761
they're all in Moscow,
Hospital Number 6.

206
00:17:33,678 --> 00:17:36,723
We need to find out exactly
what happened that night,

207
00:17:36,806 --> 00:17:40,268
moment by moment,
decision by decision.

208
00:17:41,686 --> 00:17:43,688
Go now while they're still alive.

209
00:17:43,772 --> 00:17:45,982
Talk to them.

210
00:17:46,066 --> 00:17:48,652
Because if we don't find out
how this happened,

211
00:17:48,735 --> 00:17:51,029
it will happen again.

212
00:17:54,241 --> 00:17:55,951
And, Khomyuk...

213
00:17:57,327 --> 00:17:58,954
Be careful.

214
00:18:06,211 --> 00:18:07,712
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

215
00:18:07,796 --> 00:18:09,631
(ELEVATOR RATTLING)

216
00:18:23,520 --> 00:18:25,063
Well, fuck you!

217
00:18:25,146 --> 00:18:26,481
(LAUGHTER)

218
00:18:28,024 --> 00:18:29,985
Hey, here's one, here's one.

219
00:18:30,068 --> 00:18:31,987
What's as big as a house,

220
00:18:32,070 --> 00:18:35,115
burns 20 liters of fuel every hour,

221
00:18:35,198 --> 00:18:37,033
puts out a shit-load of smoke
and noise,

222
00:18:38,243 --> 00:18:40,495
and cuts an apple into three pieces?

223
00:18:43,039 --> 00:18:46,501
A Soviet machine made to cut
apples into four pieces!

224
00:18:46,584 --> 00:18:48,044
(LAUGHTER)

225
00:19:25,832 --> 00:19:28,293
-Who's in charge here?
-GLUKHOV: I'm the crew chief.

226
00:19:29,961 --> 00:19:33,173
I am Shadov,
Minister of Coal Industries.

227
00:19:33,256 --> 00:19:34,549
We know who you are.

228
00:19:36,760 --> 00:19:38,428
How many men do you have?

229
00:19:39,012 --> 00:19:42,515
On this shift, 45 here,
a hundred in total.

230
00:19:43,433 --> 00:19:46,394
I need all 100 men to gather
their equipment and get in the trucks.

231
00:19:47,645 --> 00:19:50,065
Do you? To where?

232
00:19:51,816 --> 00:19:53,026
That's classified.

233
00:19:59,741 --> 00:20:00,909
Come on, then.

234
00:20:01,493 --> 00:20:02,744
Start shooting.

235
00:20:03,203 --> 00:20:05,914
You haven't got enough
bullets for all of us.

236
00:20:05,997 --> 00:20:08,166
Kill as many as you can,
whoever's left,

237
00:20:08,500 --> 00:20:10,126
they'll beat the living piss
out of each of you.

238
00:20:10,210 --> 00:20:12,462
-You can't talk to us like that!
-Shut the fuck up!

239
00:20:13,630 --> 00:20:16,132
This is Tula. This is our mine.

240
00:20:17,175 --> 00:20:18,968
We don't leave unless we know why.

241
00:20:21,012 --> 00:20:22,097
Mmm.

242
00:20:26,267 --> 00:20:28,269
You're going to Chernobyl.

243
00:20:30,397 --> 00:20:31,981
Do you know what's happened there?

244
00:20:33,108 --> 00:20:35,110
We dig up coal, not bodies.

245
00:20:36,277 --> 00:20:38,571
The reactor fuel is going
to sink into the ground

246
00:20:38,655 --> 00:20:41,574
and poison the water
from Kiev to the Black Sea.

247
00:20:41,658 --> 00:20:42,992
All of it.

248
00:20:44,119 --> 00:20:45,620
Forever, they say.

249
00:20:47,747 --> 00:20:50,291
They want you
to stop that from happening.

250
00:20:51,668 --> 00:20:53,837
And how are we supposed to do that?

251
00:20:54,671 --> 00:20:57,298
They didn't tell me,
because I don't need to know.

252
00:20:59,259 --> 00:21:01,761
Do you need to know,
or have you heard enough?

253
00:21:35,628 --> 00:21:37,213
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

254
00:21:43,011 --> 00:21:45,805
Now you look like
the Minister of Coal.

255
00:22:05,200 --> 00:22:06,409
(VASILY GROANS)

256
00:22:07,368 --> 00:22:08,786
Vasya?

257
00:22:10,246 --> 00:22:11,498
Vasya?

258
00:22:12,874 --> 00:22:14,751
(SHALLOW BREATHING)

259
00:22:17,670 --> 00:22:18,880
VASILY: No, no, no.

260
00:22:19,881 --> 00:22:21,716
They told you no touching.

261
00:22:22,217 --> 00:22:24,469
It's not safe.

262
00:22:24,552 --> 00:22:26,804
(KISSING) They touch you.

263
00:22:27,889 --> 00:22:29,807
If it's safe for them,
it's safe for me.

264
00:22:39,901 --> 00:22:41,736
Where are the others?

265
00:22:41,819 --> 00:22:43,655
They took them to a special room.

266
00:22:45,323 --> 00:22:46,950
They won't tell me where.

267
00:22:51,246 --> 00:22:52,372
Will you open the curtains?

268
00:22:53,873 --> 00:22:54,874
Hmm?

269
00:22:55,166 --> 00:22:56,543
Open the curtains.

270
00:23:00,630 --> 00:23:01,631
Ah.

271
00:23:13,810 --> 00:23:15,895
(LAUGHS)

272
00:23:19,190 --> 00:23:21,359
Please, tell me what you see outside.

273
00:23:22,443 --> 00:23:23,945
Tell me everything.

274
00:23:31,452 --> 00:23:32,453
Um...

275
00:23:34,247 --> 00:23:36,207
I can see the Red Square.

276
00:23:39,294 --> 00:23:40,420
And

277
00:23:41,296 --> 00:23:43,089
the Kremlin.

278
00:23:44,382 --> 00:23:47,552
Spasskaya Tower, the mausoleum.

279
00:23:50,013 --> 00:23:51,681
You see St. Basil's?

280
00:23:53,308 --> 00:23:54,809
Yeah.

281
00:23:54,892 --> 00:23:56,603
-VASILY: Ah.
(CHUCKLES)

282
00:23:56,894 --> 00:23:58,605
Yes, it's beautiful.

283
00:24:00,148 --> 00:24:02,108
I told you.

284
00:24:02,191 --> 00:24:04,944
I told you I'd show you Moscow,
didn't I?

285
00:24:05,153 --> 00:24:06,237
Huh?

286
00:24:06,321 --> 00:24:08,323
Yeah. Yes.

287
00:24:14,287 --> 00:24:16,080
Thank you.

288
00:25:03,378 --> 00:25:06,047
I'm not eating that. It's shit.

289
00:25:06,881 --> 00:25:08,091
Get me something else.

290
00:25:09,467 --> 00:25:11,928
I'm not a nurse, Comrade Dyatlov.

291
00:25:12,011 --> 00:25:13,846
I'm a nuclear physicist.

292
00:25:14,806 --> 00:25:17,225
Well, then, Comrade Nuclear Physicist,

293
00:25:18,768 --> 00:25:23,272
unless you happen to have
a butter and caviar sandwich on you,

294
00:25:23,356 --> 00:25:25,692
you can get the fuck out of my room.

295
00:26:27,587 --> 00:26:28,671
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

296
00:26:44,604 --> 00:26:45,855
What?

297
00:26:46,939 --> 00:26:48,524
I'm not good at this, Boris.

298
00:26:49,567 --> 00:26:51,402
The lying.

299
00:26:55,823 --> 00:26:58,326
Have you ever spent time with miners?

300
00:27:00,244 --> 00:27:01,579
No.

301
00:27:01,746 --> 00:27:04,373
My advice, tell the truth.

302
00:27:04,457 --> 00:27:07,835
These men work in the dark.
They see everything.

303
00:27:09,337 --> 00:27:11,672
Andrei GLUKHOV, crew chief.

304
00:27:27,271 --> 00:27:28,439
Do these work?

305
00:27:30,233 --> 00:27:31,776
To an extent.

306
00:27:35,071 --> 00:27:36,072
Of course.

307
00:27:48,251 --> 00:27:49,710
So what's the job?

308
00:27:51,712 --> 00:27:55,424
We need to install a liquid
nitrogen heat exchanger

309
00:27:55,508 --> 00:27:58,719
underneath this concrete pad.

310
00:27:58,803 --> 00:28:02,473
There's no way to approach
from the interior of the building,

311
00:28:02,557 --> 00:28:04,892
so you have to get at it
from underground.

312
00:28:04,976 --> 00:28:08,437
-And what's above the pad?
-The core of the nuclear reactor,

313
00:28:08,521 --> 00:28:10,857
which is melting down.

314
00:28:12,358 --> 00:28:14,026
What? Like...

315
00:28:15,736 --> 00:28:16,863
Essentially.

316
00:28:18,865 --> 00:28:20,199
Is it gonna fall on top of us?

317
00:28:20,283 --> 00:28:22,076
Not if you're done within six weeks.

318
00:28:24,036 --> 00:28:25,997
Dimensions?

319
00:28:29,041 --> 00:28:31,002
Break ground here,

320
00:28:31,085 --> 00:28:33,462
dig a tunnel 150 meters to here,

321
00:28:33,546 --> 00:28:36,507
excavate a space 30 by 30 meters

322
00:28:36,591 --> 00:28:38,384
for the heat exchanger.

323
00:28:38,467 --> 00:28:41,554
And because we need to keep disruption
of the ground above to a minimum,

324
00:28:41,637 --> 00:28:43,431
you can't use any heavy machinery.

325
00:28:43,514 --> 00:28:44,932
It has to be done by hand.

326
00:28:45,766 --> 00:28:47,685
Gonna need more men.

327
00:28:48,769 --> 00:28:50,146
Four hundred at least.

328
00:28:50,229 --> 00:28:52,773
We'll have to work around the clock.

329
00:28:52,857 --> 00:28:54,609
How deep do you want this tunnel?
Six meters?

330
00:28:54,692 --> 00:28:57,737
-Twelve.
-Twelve? Why?

331
00:28:57,945 --> 00:29:00,406
For your protection.

332
00:29:00,489 --> 00:29:04,368
At that depth, you'll be shielded
from much of the radiation.

333
00:29:05,202 --> 00:29:08,497
The entrance to the tunnel
won't be 12 meters below ground.

334
00:29:09,790 --> 00:29:11,667
No.

335
00:29:11,751 --> 00:29:14,629
And we're not 12 meters
below ground now.

336
00:29:19,342 --> 00:29:22,219
No. We're not.

337
00:29:25,139 --> 00:29:27,183
SHCHERBINA: We have
some equipment here on site.

338
00:29:28,225 --> 00:29:30,269
More will arrive by midnight.

339
00:29:31,812 --> 00:29:33,189
You can start in the morning.

340
00:29:33,272 --> 00:29:35,149
No. We start now.

341
00:29:35,942 --> 00:29:39,737
I don't want my men here
one more second than they need to be.

342
00:29:41,030 --> 00:29:44,450
If these worked,
you'd be wearing them.

343
00:29:49,288 --> 00:29:52,291
-(DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES)
(EXHALES)

344
00:29:54,627 --> 00:29:56,170
Are they all like that?

345
00:29:57,004 --> 00:29:58,714
They're all like that.

346
00:30:20,152 --> 00:30:21,570
(MEN GRUNTING)

347
00:31:22,465 --> 00:31:23,466
MAN ON PHONE: Yes?

348
00:31:24,133 --> 00:31:25,301
What's it up to?

349
00:31:25,384 --> 00:31:26,677
Uh, 50 degrees.

350
00:31:30,639 --> 00:31:31,640
Fuck!

351
00:31:36,187 --> 00:31:37,271
Hey!

352
00:31:38,481 --> 00:31:39,565
Hey, you!

353
00:31:49,116 --> 00:31:50,534
We need fans.

354
00:31:50,618 --> 00:31:52,203
For what purpose?

355
00:31:52,536 --> 00:31:54,038
What do you mean, "For what purpose?"

356
00:31:54,121 --> 00:31:55,915
To dig your fucking tunnel,
that's why.

357
00:31:55,998 --> 00:31:57,792
-Who's talking to you?
-Whoa, whoa. Comrades.

358
00:31:59,126 --> 00:32:00,544
It's 50 degrees down there.

359
00:32:01,504 --> 00:32:04,548
We can't breathe without the masks,
we can't breathe with the masks.

360
00:32:04,632 --> 00:32:07,510
It's like a fucking oven.
We need ventilation.

361
00:32:07,593 --> 00:32:10,513
Fans will put dust in the air,
the dust will go in your lungs.

362
00:32:10,596 --> 00:32:13,099
I've been breathing dust
in my lungs for 20 years.

363
00:32:13,182 --> 00:32:15,976
Not this dust. I'm sorry.

364
00:32:16,060 --> 00:32:18,437
For your own good, no fans.

365
00:32:37,289 --> 00:32:38,833
(STRAINED BREATHING)

366
00:32:47,383 --> 00:32:49,718
My name is Ulana Khomyuk.

367
00:32:49,802 --> 00:32:52,638
I'm a nuclear physicist
with the Chernobyl Commission.

368
00:32:54,932 --> 00:32:57,393
I want you to tell me
everything that happened

369
00:32:57,476 --> 00:32:58,686
on the night of the accident.

370
00:33:00,396 --> 00:33:01,564
Is that all right?

371
00:33:04,567 --> 00:33:05,609
Yes.

372
00:33:07,945 --> 00:33:09,155
I want to tell.

373
00:33:10,364 --> 00:33:11,407
KHOMYUK: All right.

374
00:33:24,753 --> 00:33:27,089
Your official title was?

375
00:33:30,301 --> 00:33:35,264
My name is Leonid Fedorovych Toptunov.

376
00:33:36,182 --> 00:33:41,437
I am the Senior Reactor Control
Chief Engineer

377
00:33:41,520 --> 00:33:43,522
at Chernobyl Nuclear Power Plant.

378
00:33:47,610 --> 00:33:49,528
KHOMYUK: Senior engineer?

379
00:33:51,864 --> 00:33:52,948
How old are you?

380
00:33:58,662 --> 00:34:00,039
(STRAINED BREATHING) I'm 25.

381
00:34:48,545 --> 00:34:50,547
VASILY: Lyusya? Lyusya?

382
00:34:50,631 --> 00:34:52,883
Yes, I'm here, I'm here. I'm...

383
00:35:07,815 --> 00:35:09,233
Have you been here this whole time?

384
00:35:09,900 --> 00:35:11,360
No one said I should leave.

385
00:35:12,278 --> 00:35:13,320
I did.

386
00:35:13,988 --> 00:35:15,281
Thirty minutes, I said!

387
00:35:15,364 --> 00:35:18,325
Well, where have you been?
When he's in pain?

388
00:35:18,909 --> 00:35:20,452
When his sores stick to his gown?

389
00:35:20,536 --> 00:35:21,954
When he soils himself
five times a night?

390
00:35:22,037 --> 00:35:23,872
I've been looking after him.
Where have you been?

391
00:35:23,956 --> 00:35:25,666
I've been in the north and west wing,

392
00:35:25,749 --> 00:35:28,627
where there are dozens of patients
from Chernobyl exactly like him.

393
00:35:29,378 --> 00:35:30,963
-It isn't safe for you here.
-He's my husband.

394
00:35:31,046 --> 00:35:32,089
Not anymore.

395
00:35:32,172 --> 00:35:34,133
He's something else now.
Do you understand?

396
00:35:34,216 --> 00:35:35,509
He's dangerous to you.

397
00:35:36,802 --> 00:35:38,846
-He's burned.
-(SIGHS)

398
00:35:39,555 --> 00:35:40,889
Go home.

399
00:35:41,890 --> 00:35:42,933
Please.

400
00:35:46,478 --> 00:35:48,731
It won't take much longer. I, uh...

401
00:35:52,860 --> 00:35:54,486
I don't want him to die alone.

402
00:35:58,240 --> 00:35:59,908
Stay on the other side of the plastic,

403
00:36:02,036 --> 00:36:03,495
or I'll have you removed by security.

404
00:36:12,421 --> 00:36:13,589
(DOOR OPENS)

405
00:36:14,965 --> 00:36:15,966
(DOOR CLOSES)

406
00:36:19,845 --> 00:36:21,555
(VASILY BREATHING HEAVILY)

407
00:37:03,013 --> 00:37:04,640
-VASILY: Lyusya?
-Yes, my love.

408
00:37:08,560 --> 00:37:09,645
Is it day?

409
00:37:11,105 --> 00:37:13,107
No, it's nighttime now.

410
00:37:17,236 --> 00:37:18,570
I think I had a dream,

411
00:37:19,154 --> 00:37:20,572
it's just gone.

412
00:37:22,783 --> 00:37:23,951
Vasya.

413
00:37:30,124 --> 00:37:31,834
We're going to have a baby.

414
00:38:01,238 --> 00:38:02,239
(DOOR OPENS)

415
00:38:03,949 --> 00:38:04,950
(DOOR CLOSES)

416
00:38:08,871 --> 00:38:10,038
The fire's out.

417
00:38:12,749 --> 00:38:13,959
It's out, Valera.

418
00:38:15,669 --> 00:38:17,880
The miners are making
incredible progress.

419
00:38:19,381 --> 00:38:22,217
They say the whole job
will be finished in four weeks.

420
00:38:23,969 --> 00:38:24,970
Four weeks.

421
00:38:26,305 --> 00:38:27,389
Can you believe that?

422
00:38:34,146 --> 00:38:35,689
I know the job isn't over.

423
00:38:37,816 --> 00:38:39,359
But it's the beginning of the end.

424
00:38:42,654 --> 00:38:44,281
-(KNOCK ON DOOR)
-(DOOR OPENS)

425
00:38:45,449 --> 00:38:47,784
I'm sorry to bother you,
Deputy Minister,

426
00:38:50,412 --> 00:38:51,413
but it is the miners.

427
00:39:22,444 --> 00:39:23,570
(INDISTINCT TALKING)

428
00:39:39,753 --> 00:39:40,796
What?

429
00:39:41,255 --> 00:39:43,549
You wouldn't give us fans,
it's too hot for clothes.

430
00:39:43,924 --> 00:39:46,343
So we're digging the old way.
This is the way our fathers mined.

431
00:39:49,012 --> 00:39:50,472
We're still wearing the fucking hats.

432
00:39:51,431 --> 00:39:52,516
What do you want?

433
00:39:55,644 --> 00:39:57,813
You're not as protected now.

434
00:39:58,564 --> 00:40:00,107
Are you telling me
it will make a difference?

435
00:40:06,154 --> 00:40:07,364
When this is over,

436
00:40:08,407 --> 00:40:09,616
will they be looked after?

437
00:40:13,912 --> 00:40:14,955
I don't know.

438
00:40:26,592 --> 00:40:27,593
You don't know.

439
00:40:47,195 --> 00:40:51,325
KHOMYUK: So the power level jumped
from 200 to 400 megawatts?

440
00:40:52,951 --> 00:40:53,994
Yes.

441
00:40:55,078 --> 00:40:56,204
Very fast.

442
00:40:57,998 --> 00:41:01,001
Why didn't you initiate
an emergency shutdown?

443
00:41:01,543 --> 00:41:03,837
Why didn't you press the AZ-5 button?

444
00:41:05,672 --> 00:41:06,673
We did.

445
00:41:07,924 --> 00:41:10,761
I reported the increase to Akimov,

446
00:41:10,844 --> 00:41:12,304
and he pressed the button.

447
00:41:13,972 --> 00:41:16,350
Leonid, that's... That's not possible.

448
00:41:18,602 --> 00:41:19,645
He did.

449
00:41:20,687 --> 00:41:21,938
I swear.

450
00:41:22,981 --> 00:41:24,399
I saw him do it.

451
00:41:28,320 --> 00:41:30,405
And that's when it exploded.

452
00:41:33,241 --> 00:41:34,242
KHOMYUK: What?

453
00:41:37,204 --> 00:41:38,205
(DOOR OPENS)

454
00:41:48,924 --> 00:41:49,925
KHOMYUK: Um...

455
00:41:51,259 --> 00:41:52,678
Which room is Akimov?

456
00:41:52,761 --> 00:41:53,762
NURSE: Twenty-seven.

457
00:42:01,561 --> 00:42:04,106
(BREATHING RAGGEDLY)

458
00:42:09,069 --> 00:42:12,447
AKIMOV: I pressed it,
before the explosion.

459
00:42:12,948 --> 00:42:14,116
Before.

460
00:42:17,119 --> 00:42:18,412
But why?

461
00:42:19,663 --> 00:42:20,914
Why would that happen?

462
00:42:23,125 --> 00:42:26,002
I shut it down. I pressed AZ-5.

463
00:42:32,300 --> 00:42:33,719
KHOMYUK: Thank you, Comrade Akimov.

464
00:42:39,057 --> 00:42:40,559
AKIMOV: I did everything right.

465
00:42:42,602 --> 00:42:44,020
I did everything right.

466
00:43:15,552 --> 00:43:16,595
KHOMYUK: Get out.

467
00:43:17,429 --> 00:43:18,722
Get out. Get out of here.

468
00:43:18,805 --> 00:43:21,141
Let me go! Let me go!

469
00:43:21,224 --> 00:43:23,518
Stop it! Stop it!

470
00:43:26,772 --> 00:43:29,399
You let her in that room?
Inside the plastic, touching him?

471
00:43:29,483 --> 00:43:30,859
Did you know she's pregnant?

472
00:43:30,942 --> 00:43:32,110
It's not true!

473
00:43:32,194 --> 00:43:33,403
What have you done?

474
00:43:33,487 --> 00:43:35,739
What kind of a place is this?
Where is her protection?

475
00:43:35,822 --> 00:43:37,949
Do you have any idea
what you're dealing with?

476
00:43:38,033 --> 00:43:39,826
-Of course, I do. Please, I do not...
-No.

477
00:43:40,702 --> 00:43:42,287
-People are going to hear about this.
-Wait.

478
00:43:42,704 --> 00:43:44,456
People are going to hear.
Do you understand?

479
00:43:44,539 --> 00:43:45,582
Everyone is going to hear.

480
00:43:46,416 --> 00:43:47,918
MAN: What is everyone gonna hear?

481
00:43:54,716 --> 00:43:56,718
I am with the official
Chernobyl Commission.

482
00:43:56,802 --> 00:43:59,012
I've been authorized
by Valery Legasov.

483
00:43:59,221 --> 00:44:00,222
You can check this.

484
00:44:00,305 --> 00:44:01,807
-My name is Ulana...
-We know who you are.

485
00:44:05,352 --> 00:44:06,937
What is everyone gonna hear?

486
00:44:28,333 --> 00:44:29,459
You have your notes?

487
00:44:30,210 --> 00:44:31,294
Yes.

488
00:44:34,256 --> 00:44:35,966
Khomyuk was arrested last night.

489
00:44:36,049 --> 00:44:38,301
What? Why?

490
00:44:38,385 --> 00:44:39,553
I don't know.

491
00:44:41,304 --> 00:44:42,389
Was it...

492
00:44:43,473 --> 00:44:44,474
Of course it was.

493
00:44:46,351 --> 00:44:47,435
I'm working on it.

494
00:44:48,061 --> 00:44:50,146
-Boris...
-I'm working on it.

495
00:44:51,565 --> 00:44:52,732
What more do you want from me?

496
00:44:53,733 --> 00:44:54,776
Fix your tie.

497
00:44:59,322 --> 00:45:00,490
(DOOR OPENS)

498
00:45:01,825 --> 00:45:02,868
They'll see you now.

499
00:45:13,503 --> 00:45:16,715
After thousands of sorties,
our brave helicopter crews

500
00:45:16,798 --> 00:45:19,009
successfully extinguished the fire.

501
00:45:19,092 --> 00:45:20,927
The miners are working
heroically to ensure

502
00:45:21,011 --> 00:45:23,471
that the fuel does not
reach the groundwater.

503
00:45:23,555 --> 00:45:27,267
And furthermore, there's no longer
a threat of additional explosion.

504
00:45:27,976 --> 00:45:31,771
The Soviet people have faced
the challenge and risen to the task,

505
00:45:32,147 --> 00:45:34,691
and they and everyone in this room
are to be commended.

506
00:45:39,988 --> 00:45:42,449
Lastly, Professor Legasov
and I have been vigilant

507
00:45:42,532 --> 00:45:44,868
to protect the security
interests of the State.

508
00:45:45,201 --> 00:45:47,621
And since the unfortunate
release of information

509
00:45:47,704 --> 00:45:49,456
directly following the accident,

510
00:45:49,539 --> 00:45:51,583
we believe that there
has been no further lapse.

511
00:45:52,125 --> 00:45:53,376
Comrade Charkov,

512
00:45:54,878 --> 00:45:58,173
we hope we have lived up to
the highest standards of the KGB.

513
00:45:58,590 --> 00:45:59,674
You have.

514
00:46:00,467 --> 00:46:01,509
SHCHERBINA: Thank you.

515
00:46:02,886 --> 00:46:07,432
Professor Legasov will now speak
about the work that remains.

516
00:46:09,434 --> 00:46:10,560
Thank you.

517
00:46:14,856 --> 00:46:17,651
Deputy Chairman Shcherbina
has given you the good news,

518
00:46:17,734 --> 00:46:19,027
and it is good.

519
00:46:19,819 --> 00:46:21,947
The immediate danger is over.

520
00:46:22,530 --> 00:46:24,824
Now, I'm afraid,
a long war must begin.

521
00:46:27,035 --> 00:46:29,996
There is an enormous amount
of radioactive debris

522
00:46:30,080 --> 00:46:31,790
and contamination spread out
across a zone

523
00:46:31,873 --> 00:46:34,209
of approximately
2,600-square kilometers.

524
00:46:34,626 --> 00:46:38,630
This entire region must be
completely evacuated.

525
00:46:40,090 --> 00:46:43,301
We must go to every town,
every village to ensure this.

526
00:46:44,594 --> 00:46:49,557
And all animals still
surviving within the zone,

527
00:46:49,641 --> 00:46:52,394
whether domesticated or wild,

528
00:46:52,477 --> 00:46:56,898
must be presumed contaminated
and will have to be destroyed

529
00:46:56,982 --> 00:46:59,651
to prevent the spread
of radiation and disease.

530
00:47:01,027 --> 00:47:03,655
In the immediate area
surrounding Chernobyl,

531
00:47:03,738 --> 00:47:09,202
uh, every rock, every tree,
the very ground itself,

532
00:47:09,285 --> 00:47:12,914
has absorbed a dangerous
amount of radionuclides,

533
00:47:12,998 --> 00:47:16,376
which will be carried by the wind
and the rain if left exposed.

534
00:47:16,459 --> 00:47:18,628
So we will have to raze
entire forests.

535
00:47:18,712 --> 00:47:20,922
We will have to rip up
the top layer of earth

536
00:47:21,006 --> 00:47:22,382
and bury it under itself,

537
00:47:22,465 --> 00:47:25,468
approximately, 100 square kilometers.

538
00:47:27,762 --> 00:47:31,349
Um, and finally,
we will need to construct

539
00:47:31,433 --> 00:47:35,770
a containment structure
around the power plant itself,

540
00:47:35,854 --> 00:47:38,773
which will, of course,
still be extremely...

541
00:47:42,193 --> 00:47:43,945
There will be deaths.

542
00:47:47,615 --> 00:47:49,367
What amount of time,

543
00:47:49,451 --> 00:47:51,077
and how many men do you require?

544
00:47:51,327 --> 00:47:54,664
We expect this liquidation
effort to take three years

545
00:47:54,748 --> 00:47:57,333
and approximately 750,000 men,

546
00:47:57,417 --> 00:48:01,254
including a number of doctors
and structural engineers.

547
00:48:03,006 --> 00:48:04,299
How many deaths?

548
00:48:05,467 --> 00:48:06,718
Thousands.

549
00:48:07,510 --> 00:48:08,928
Perhaps tens of thousands.

550
00:48:17,312 --> 00:48:18,313
GORBACHEV: Begin at once.

551
00:48:24,694 --> 00:48:26,654
LEGASOV: Comrade Charkov.
SHCHERBINA: Valery!

552
00:48:28,782 --> 00:48:29,866
Yes, Professor?

553
00:48:31,117 --> 00:48:33,995
My associate was arrested last night.

554
00:48:34,537 --> 00:48:35,538
Oh?

555
00:48:36,414 --> 00:48:37,665
I mean no disrespect,

556
00:48:37,749 --> 00:48:39,709
but I was wondering
if you could tell me why.

557
00:48:39,793 --> 00:48:41,836
I assure you, I don't know
who you're talking about.

558
00:48:41,920 --> 00:48:43,838
She was arrested by the KGB.

559
00:48:45,006 --> 00:48:47,884
You are the first deputy
chairman of the KGB.

560
00:48:48,343 --> 00:48:49,344
I am.

561
00:48:49,719 --> 00:48:52,305
That's why I don't have to bother
with arresting people anymore.

562
00:48:52,388 --> 00:48:54,766
But you are bothering
with having us followed.

563
00:48:56,309 --> 00:48:59,020
I think the deputy chairman is busy.

564
00:48:59,104 --> 00:49:01,064
No, no. It's perfectly understandable.

565
00:49:01,397 --> 00:49:04,067
Comrade, I know you've heard
the stories about us.

566
00:49:05,151 --> 00:49:07,445
When I hear them, even I am shocked.

567
00:49:07,529 --> 00:49:09,489
But we are not what people say.

568
00:49:09,697 --> 00:49:11,783
Yes, people are following you.

569
00:49:12,450 --> 00:49:14,077
People are following those people.

570
00:49:14,994 --> 00:49:16,037
You see them?

571
00:49:18,581 --> 00:49:19,833
They follow me.

572
00:49:20,583 --> 00:49:24,003
The KGB is a circle of accountability.

573
00:49:24,337 --> 00:49:25,839
Nothing more.

574
00:49:26,005 --> 00:49:27,507
You know the work we're doing here.

575
00:49:29,634 --> 00:49:30,969
You really don't trust us?

576
00:49:31,052 --> 00:49:32,428
Of course, I do.

577
00:49:32,929 --> 00:49:34,806
But you know the old Russian proverb.

578
00:49:35,640 --> 00:49:37,100
"Trust but verify."

579
00:49:39,727 --> 00:49:43,273
And the Americans think that
Ronald Reagan thought that up.

580
00:49:43,356 --> 00:49:44,399
Can you imagine?

581
00:49:45,608 --> 00:49:47,235
It was very nice speaking with you.

582
00:49:48,528 --> 00:49:49,737
I need her.

583
00:49:52,448 --> 00:49:54,909
So you will be accountable for her?

584
00:49:59,539 --> 00:50:00,623
Then it's done.

585
00:50:02,125 --> 00:50:04,043
-Her name is...
-I know who she is.

586
00:50:05,128 --> 00:50:06,462
Good day, Professor.

587
00:50:16,764 --> 00:50:19,809
Well, that went surprisingly well.

588
00:50:20,643 --> 00:50:22,312
You came off like a naive idiot.

589
00:50:24,022 --> 00:50:26,274
And naive idiots are not a threat.

590
00:50:42,290 --> 00:50:44,250
I'll come back when
the paperwork's complete.

591
00:50:51,424 --> 00:50:52,550
(LOCK CLICKING)

592
00:50:52,634 --> 00:50:53,760
Are you all right?

593
00:50:53,843 --> 00:50:55,053
They didn't hurt me.

594
00:50:57,305 --> 00:50:59,724
They let a pregnant woman
into a room with a...

595
00:50:59,891 --> 00:51:01,851
(EXHALES) It doesn't matter.

596
00:51:03,144 --> 00:51:04,896
They were stupid. I was stupid.

597
00:51:07,232 --> 00:51:08,566
Dyatlov won't talk to me.

598
00:51:10,360 --> 00:51:12,695
Akimov, yes, Toptunov, yes, but...

599
00:51:14,906 --> 00:51:16,074
Valery,

600
00:51:16,658 --> 00:51:17,784
Akimov...

601
00:51:19,202 --> 00:51:20,495
His face was gone.

602
00:51:23,873 --> 00:51:25,083
You want to stop?

603
00:51:27,377 --> 00:51:29,128
Is that a choice I even have?

604
00:51:37,971 --> 00:51:41,140
Do you think the fuel will actually
melt through the concrete pad?

605
00:51:41,224 --> 00:51:44,435
I don't know. A 40% chance, maybe.

606
00:51:47,647 --> 00:51:49,524
I said 50. (SCOFFS)

607
00:51:50,525 --> 00:51:52,652
Either way, the numbers
mean the same thing.

608
00:51:52,735 --> 00:51:53,820
"Maybe."

609
00:51:57,115 --> 00:51:59,617
Maybe the core will melt
through to the groundwater.

610
00:52:00,576 --> 00:52:02,829
Maybe the miners who I've told
to dig under the reactor

611
00:52:02,912 --> 00:52:04,580
will save millions of lives.

612
00:52:06,541 --> 00:52:08,167
Maybe I'm killing them for nothing.

613
00:52:12,422 --> 00:52:14,090
I don't want to do this anymore.

614
00:52:16,050 --> 00:52:17,218
I want to stop.

615
00:52:19,262 --> 00:52:20,346
But I can't.

616
00:52:22,181 --> 00:52:24,642
I don't think you have
a choice any more than I do.

617
00:52:26,644 --> 00:52:29,439
I think, despite the stupidity,

618
00:52:30,064 --> 00:52:31,899
the lies, even this,

619
00:52:32,859 --> 00:52:34,152
you are compelled.

620
00:52:35,153 --> 00:52:37,530
The problem has been assigned,
and you will stop at nothing

621
00:52:37,613 --> 00:52:38,906
until you find an answer.

622
00:52:38,990 --> 00:52:41,617
Because that is who you are.

623
00:52:43,870 --> 00:52:45,163
A lunatic, then.

624
00:52:47,749 --> 00:52:48,750
A scientist.

625
00:52:50,043 --> 00:52:51,836
(LOCK CLICKING)

626
00:53:11,022 --> 00:53:13,274
Did you know that they were
running a safety test?

627
00:53:15,151 --> 00:53:16,152
Yeah.

628
00:53:16,235 --> 00:53:17,362
There's something else.

629
00:53:19,238 --> 00:53:22,408
Akimov says
they shut the reactor down,

630
00:53:22,492 --> 00:53:24,410
and Toptunov confirms it.

631
00:53:25,078 --> 00:53:26,245
They pressed AZ-5.

632
00:53:26,537 --> 00:53:28,247
Apparently not soon enough.

633
00:53:28,748 --> 00:53:29,832
No.

634
00:53:30,458 --> 00:53:34,253
They say Akimov pressed AZ-5,

635
00:53:35,129 --> 00:53:37,090
and then the reactor exploded.

636
00:53:39,425 --> 00:53:42,178
If it had been just one of them,
I would have put it under

637
00:53:42,261 --> 00:53:45,139
faulty memory or delusion even,

638
00:53:45,223 --> 00:53:47,934
but they both agreed.
They were adamant.

639
00:53:52,563 --> 00:53:53,648
Comrade?

640
00:53:56,692 --> 00:53:57,777
Do you think it's possible?

641
00:53:57,860 --> 00:53:59,445
I think it makes no sense. I...

642
00:54:00,196 --> 00:54:03,408
I think it's what I would say if
I was trying to cover my own mistakes.

643
00:54:04,033 --> 00:54:05,034
But?

644
00:54:06,285 --> 00:54:07,453
I believe them.

645
00:54:10,289 --> 00:54:11,707
Then you should pursue it.

646
00:54:12,333 --> 00:54:14,961
We have to pursue every possibility,

647
00:54:15,837 --> 00:54:17,672
no matter how unlikely,

648
00:54:18,506 --> 00:54:20,842
no matter what or who's to blame.

649
00:54:23,136 --> 00:54:26,389
I'll go back to the hospital
and re-interview Akimov and Toptunov.

650
00:54:29,892 --> 00:54:30,977
If they're still awake.

651
00:54:32,770 --> 00:54:33,813
They're not.

652
00:54:36,149 --> 00:54:37,150
MAN: Khomyuk.

653
00:55:32,497 --> 00:55:34,957
(MAN SPEAKING IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

